7:["$","$Lc",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does Bluefin settle W/USDT funding payments?","answer":"Bluefin settles funding payments every hour for all perpetual pairs including W/USDT. This frequent settlement cycle allows for more responsive rate adjustments compared to traditional 8-hour cycles on other exchanges."},{"question":"What are the trading fees for W/USDT perpetuals on Bluefin?","answer":"Bluefin charges 0.02% maker fees and 0.05% taker fees for W/USDT perpetual futures. The low maker fee structure makes it attractive for market makers and funding rate arbitrage strategies that require frequent position adjustments."},{"question":"Can I trade W/USDT on Bluefin without KYC?","answer":"Yes, Bluefin operates as a decentralized exchange on Sui, allowing W/USDT perpetual trading through wallet connections without KYC requirements. However, users must bridge USDT to Sui and ensure sufficient gas tokens for transaction fees."},{"question":"What are the typical funding rate ranges for W/USDT on Bluefin?","answer":"W/USDT funding rates on Bluefin typically range from -0.2% to +0.4% during normal market conditions, with extreme periods seeing rates between -0.5% to +0.8%. The rates tend to be more volatile than major pairs due to smaller trading volumes and infrastructure token correlation patterns."}]}]
